fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.bank

Class Client

  • java.lang.Object
    • fr.sorbonne_u.devs_simulation.examples.bank.Client
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    EventInformationI, java.io.Serializable

    public class Client
extends java.lang.Object
implements EventInformationI
    The class Client represents a client to be served at the bank.

    Description

    This class materialises a client at the bank. It is used here merely to store the time of arrival of the client to be able to compute the total time passed in the bank when its service will finish.

    Invariant

     invariant       id != null && !id.isEmpty()
 invariant       timeOfArrival != null

    Created on : 2021-11-09

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
